{"title_page": "Legendary Giant Beast Wolfman vs. Godzilla", "text_new": "{{short description|Unreleased 1983 Japanese film}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Films|date=July 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name            = Legendary Giant Beast Wolfman vs. Godzilla\n| image           = File:Wolfman vs Godzilla Poster.jpg\n| caption         = Mock-up poster\n| director        = Shizuo Nakajima\n| producer        = Shizuo Nakajima\n| screenplay      = \n| story           = \n| starring        = Ema Ishihara\n| music           = [[Akira Ifukube]] (stock)\n| cinematography  = \n| editing         = \n| studio          = \n| distributor     = \n| released        = \n| runtime         = \n| country         = Japan\n| language        = Japanese\n| budget          = \n| gross           = \n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Legendary Giant Beast Wolfman vs. Godzilla'''''<ref name=\"Mark\"/>|\u4f1d\u8aac\u306e\u5de8\u7363\u72fc\u7537\u5bfe\u30b4\u30b8\u30e9|Densetsu no Kyoj\u016b \u014ckami Otoko tai Gojira}} is an unreleased [[fan film]] directed and produced by Shizuo Nakajima.\n\n==Production==\nDirector Shizuo Nakajima conceived the idea for the film during his employment with [[Toho]] as a production assistant. He envisioned it as a feature length film with human drama and location shots and as a love-letter to [[Eiji Tsuburaya]]'s works, however, Nakajima also drew inspiration from ''[[The Curse of the Werewolf]]''. The team purchased materials directly from Toho and built miniature industrial factories, buildings, and a replica of the 1964 Godzilla suit. Using former Toho employees, principal photography began in 1983 and wrapped in the mid-80s, with 10 hours of raw footage completed. The film was shot on [[8 mm film]]. Post production is currently continuing on the film.<ref name=\"Mark\">{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2013/06/03/in-search-of-monsters-wolfman-vs-godzilla/|title=In Search of Monsters: Wolfman vs. Godzilla|author=Mark Jaramillo|work=SciFi Japan|date=June 2, 2013|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412013622/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2013/06/03/in-search-of-monsters-wolfman-vs-godzilla/}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film has remained unreleased due to litigation from Toho (owners of Godzilla) for unauthorized use of Godzilla.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/167653/lost-fan-film-godzilla-vs-legendary-wolfman-might-not-lost-much-longer/|title=Lost Fan Film Godzilla vs. Legendary Wolfman Might Not Be Lost Much Longer|author=Foywonder|work=Dread Central|date=May 22, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412015609/https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/167653/lost-fan-film-godzilla-vs-legendary-wolfman-might-not-lost-much-longer/}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Godzilla}}\n{{The Wolf Man}}\n{{film-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Fan films based on Godzilla]]\n[[Category:Unofficial adaptations]]\n[[Category:Werewolves in film]]\n[[Category:Fan films]]\n", "text_old": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Godzilla vs. Legendary Wolfman''}}\n{{short description|Unreleased 1983 Japanese film}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Films|date=July 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name            = Legendary Giant Beast Wolfman vs. Godzilla\n| image           = File:Wolfman vs Godzilla Poster.jpg\n| caption         = Mock-up poster\n| director        = Shizuo Nakajima\n| producer        = Shizuo Nakajima\n| screenplay      = \n| story           = \n| starring        = Ema Ishihara\n| music           = [[Akira Ifukube]] (stock)\n| cinematography  = \n| editing         = \n| studio          = \n| distributor     = \n| released        = \n| runtime         = \n| country         = Japan\n| language        = Japanese\n| budget          = \n| gross           = \n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Legendary Giant Beast Wolfman vs. Godzilla'''''<ref name=\"Mark\"/>|\u4f1d\u8aac\u306e\u5de8\u7363\u72fc\u7537\u5bfe\u30b4\u30b8\u30e9|Densetsu no Kyoj\u016b \u014ckami Otoko tai Gojira}} is an unreleased [[fan film]] directed and produced by Shizuo Nakajima.\n\n==Production==\nDirector Shizuo Nakajima conceived the idea for the film during his employment with [[Toho]] as a production assistant. He envisioned it as a feature length film with human drama and location shots and as a love-letter to [[Eiji Tsuburaya]]'s works, however, Nakajima also drew inspiration from ''[[The Curse of the Werewolf]]''. The team purchased materials directly from Toho and built miniature industrial factories, buildings, and a replica of the 1964 Godzilla suit. Using former Toho employees, principal photography began in 1983 and wrapped in the mid-80s, with 10 hours of raw footage completed. The film was shot on [[8 mm film]]. Post production is currently continuing on the film.<ref name=\"Mark\">{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2013/06/03/in-search-of-monsters-wolfman-vs-godzilla/|title=In Search of Monsters: Wolfman vs. Godzilla|author=Mark Jaramillo|work=SciFi Japan|date=June 2, 2013|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412013622/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2013/06/03/in-search-of-monsters-wolfman-vs-godzilla/}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film has remained unreleased due to litigation from Toho (owners of Godzilla) for unauthorized use of Godzilla.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/167653/lost-fan-film-godzilla-vs-legendary-wolfman-might-not-lost-much-longer/|title=Lost Fan Film Godzilla vs. Legendary Wolfman Might Not Be Lost Much Longer|author=Foywonder|work=Dread Central|date=May 22, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412015609/https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/167653/lost-fan-film-godzilla-vs-legendary-wolfman-might-not-lost-much-longer/}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n