e}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Works Progress Administration|authorlink=Works Progress Administration|title=The WPA guide to Illinois: the Federal Writers' Project guide to 1930s Illinois|year=1983|origyear=1939|publisher=Pantheon Books|location=New York|isbn=978-0-394-72195-8|oclc=239788752|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/wpaguidetoillino00unit}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Sister project links|Illinois|voy=Illinois}}\n* [https://www2.illinois.gov/ Illinois.gov]\n* {{curlie|Regional/North_America/United_States/Illinois}}\n* [http://www.enjoyillinois.com/ Illinois Bureau of Tourism]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070219020432/http://www.usgs.gov/state/state.asp?State=IL Illinois: Science In Your Backyard] USGS\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081201092400/http://tonto.eia.doe.gov/state/state_energy_profiles.cfm?sid=IL Illinois State Energy Profile] DOE, Energy Information Administration\n* [http://www.ers.usda.gov/data-products/state-fact-sheets/state-data.aspx?StateFIPS=17&StateName=Illinois Illinois: State Fact Sheets] USDA, Economic Research Service\n* [https://www.loc.gov/rr/program/bib/states/illinois// Illinois State Guide] LOC, Virtual Programs & Services\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081120204024/http://www.onlinebiographies.info/gov/il/index.htm Biographies Of Governors of Illinois: 1818 to 1885] compiled by OnlineBiographies.info\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120204041104/http://www.n9jig.com/ Illinois Highways Page] by Richard Carlson\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110315055644/http://www.library.illinois.edu/doc/collections/stateofillinois.html State of Illinois] research information guide from the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080515221109/http://wikis.ala.org/godort/index.php/Illinois Illinois State Agency Databases] compiled by the Government Documents Round Table (GODORT) of the American Library Association\n* {{OSM relation|122586}}\n<br />\n{{s-start}